"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-when-will-tatjana-smith-next-be-in-action-at-the-paris-olympics-2024-question-exclusive-breaking-news-result-date-time-venue-gold-medal\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9997343561397461, \"rank\": 0.00026488858581605134, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhen will Tatjana Smith next be in action at the Paris Olympics 2024?\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9997343561397461, \"rank\": 0.00026488858581605134, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africans do not have to wait long for Tatjana Smith to return to the pool at the Paris La Defense Arena.\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smithstormed to victory in the women's 100m breaststroke at theParis Olympics 2024on Monday evening, giving South Africa its first gold medal of the Games.\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3011002565029342e-15, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ATKV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATKV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith surged late to touch the wall first in a time of1:05:28, finishing ahead of China'sQianting Tang(1:05:54), with Ireland'sMona McSharryin third (1:05.59).\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tributes were quick to pour in, including fromchicken fast food chain Nando's.\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africans do not have to wait long for Smith to return to the pool at the Paris La Defense Arena.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith is the defending Olympic champion in thewomen's 200m breaststrokehaving won gold at the postponed Tokyo Olympics 2020.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Japan, Smith set a new Olympic and world record in the event, timing2:18.95in the final which took place exactly three years agoTODAY.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.6622206874709595, \"rank\": 0.28057989676026557, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 1111, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smith_set\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Smith set\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smith_set\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smith_set\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That world record was then smashed by Russian swimmerEvgeniia Chikunova, who set2:17.55in Kazan, Russia in April 2023.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.7770158800444473, \"rank\": 0.2869295017971992, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.4938686266491505e-11, \"text\": \"Kazan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazan\"}, {\"begin\": 1337, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9986020856886186, \"rank\": 0.0009669805927897018, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Chikunova isNOTat the Paris Olympics 2024.\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, only23swimmers are entered into the heats for the women's 200m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The three heats will take place on Wednesday, 31 July, starting at11:00(SA time).\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smith and Team South Africa's second entrant in the event,Kaylene Corbett, have both been drawn in Heat 1.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Team South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1649, \"end\": 1664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\", \"score\": 0.9999999961760295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylene Corbett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In something of a waste of time, the 23 starters will be reduced to 16 for the semi-finals starting at21:51(SA time), also on Wednesday, 31 July.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top 8 will race the final onThursday, 1 Augustat21:04(SA time).\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith will be the overwhelming favourite to defend her Olympic crown and add a second gold medal to her tally in Paris.\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999996493898, \"rank\": 3.504214865386497e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Smith pocketedR400 000for her win in the women's 100m breaststroke thanks to the financial incentives promised by theSouth African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc).\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith's coach, Rocco Meiring, will earn R100 000 for his role's in Smith's victory.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"IndividualsGold medallists R400 000 and the coach R100 000Silver medallists R200 000 and the coach R50 000Bronze medallists R75 000 and the coach R25 000  In addition, as reported byThe South African website, new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, promised that he has a 'big surprise' for all Team SA medal winners, suggesting there could be more prize money coming their way.\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"score\": 0.9634108711086189, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"R75\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R75_(South_Africa)\"}, {\"begin\": 2634, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.209537756188261e-24, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2834, \"end\": 2837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999388203084846, \"rank\": 6.118324870025443e-05, \"text\": \"WIN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\"}, {\"begin\": 2838, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"score\": 0.9850900535465559, \"rank\": 0.0150841375967285, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the are